From cd645e73baf20d0c2f50885c6a59209fb006e13d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Palletizer CI Fix <ci-fix@grimaldi.engineering>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 10:08:38 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(ci): make repo pass ruff 0.15.x and pin ruff for
 reproducible CI

The CI lint gate broke because the dev extra pinned ruff>=0.4.0 (unpinned), so CI
pulled ruff 0.15.20, which added rules (UP045 X|None, UP041, UP042, RUF059, ...)
that flagged both the new construction files and pre-existing core/gateway code.
Tests and the web build were unaffected.

- Resolve all 114 ruff findings: modernize typing (List/Dict/Optional -> builtins
  and X|None), sort imports, drop unused imports/locals, rename ambiguous 'l',
  zip(..., strict=False), contextlib.suppress, en-dash -> hyphen in docstrings.
- EdgeState keeps (str, Enum) with a targeted noqa: UP042 to preserve the string
  formatting used in telemetry/logs (StrEnum would change str output).
- Pin ruff==0.15.20 in the dev extra so CI lint is deterministic and a future
  ruff release can't silently turn main red again.

Verified: ruff check . -> All checks passed; pytest -> 75 passed; console script OK.
